==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|abolisshen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|frm|en}} {{term|abolir||to abolish|lang=frm}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|abolēre||destroy, cause to die out}}, present active infinitive of {{m|la|aboleō||destroy, abolish}}, {{term|abolesco||to wither, to decay|lang=la}},<ref>{{R:RHCD|page=4}}</ref> from {{term|ab||from, away from|lang=la}} + {{m|la|oleō||to grow}}.<ref>{{R:MW3 1976|page=4}}</ref>

